# B65 — NewsPWA Cursor Rules

## Project Identity
- App display name: **B65** (not "News")
- UI language: **German**
- Purpose: personal tech/IT RSS news aggregator PWA

## Stack
- Vue 3 + `<script setup lang="ts">` (Composition API only — no Options API)
- TypeScript strict mode
- Pinia for all state
- Vue Router for navigation
- Tailwind CSS 4 for styling
- Vite as build tool
- `vite-plugin-pwa` + Workbox for PWA/Service Worker

## Code Rules

### Vue Components
- Always use `<script setup lang="ts">`
- No Options API, no class components
- Use `@/` alias for all src imports: `import { useNewsStore } from '@/stores/newsStore'`

### TypeScript
- All code must be fully typed
- Use `NewsItem` from `@/types/news.ts` for article objects
- No `any` unless absolutely unavoidable

### Styling
- Tailwind utility classes only
- No custom CSS unless no Tailwind equivalent exists

### State
- All state lives in Pinia (`src/stores/newsStore.ts`)
- Never write to `localStorage` directly from components or services
- Only the store manages persistence

### Data Fetching
- Never fetch RSS feeds directly (CORS) — always use the proxy
- Proxy URL: `${VITE_API_BASE_URL}?url=<encoded-rss-url>`
- All fetch logic belongs in `src/services/feedService.ts`

## Project Structure
```
src/
  main.ts              # entry
  App.vue              # root layout
  components/
    AppHeader.vue      # filter chips
    NewsCard.vue       # article card
  config/feeds.ts      # default feed list
  router/index.ts      # routes
  services/feedService.ts  # proxy + XML parsing
  stores/newsStore.ts  # Pinia store
  types/news.ts        # NewsItem interface
  views/
    HomeView.vue       # feed grid
    SettingsView.vue   # feed management
```

## Dev Commands
```sh
npm run dev          # localhost:5173
npm run build        # type-check + build
npm run type-check   # vue-tsc only
npm run deploy       # build + rsync
```

## Environment
- `VITE_API_BASE_URL` — proxy API base URL
- `RSYNC_DEST` — deploy rsync target
- Both `.env` files are gitignored — never commit them

## Off-limits
- `dist/` — do not edit, gitignored
- Scaffold files (`HelloWorld.vue`, `TheWelcome.vue`, `WelcomeItem.vue`, `src/components/icons/`) — unused leftovers, ignore or delete
